  <h3>Why Pearl is my favorite exploration of grief in fictional media</h3>
  <h5>06 Feb 2026</h5>
  
  <div class="blog-bg">
  <p class="indented">
    For many years, Pearl from <em class="special">Steven Universe</em> has been my absolute favorite representation of grief in any form of fictional media.
  </p>
  
  <p class="indented">
    <em class="special">Steven Universe</em> is a show in which a few members of an alien species called <em>Gems</em> from a group called the <em>Crystal Gems</em> lives on Earth with a half-Gem half-human boy named Steven. The leader of the <em>Crystal Gems</em>, <span class="super-special">Rose Quartz</span>, chose to give up her physical form to fuse her magical body with human DNA in order to have a "human" baby.
  </p>
  </div>
